---
import MainLayout from "../../components/MainLayout.astro";
import { buildCollectionPageSchema } from "../../utils/schema";

const canonicalPath = "/insights";
const title = "Insights";
const summary =
  "Structured research on warehouse automation, robotics deployment, industrial AI, and 3PL markets.";
const schema = [
  buildCollectionPageSchema({
    name: title,
    description: summary,
    canonicalPath,
  }),
];
---

<MainLayout
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  title={title}
  summary={summary}
  seoTitle="Insights | Autonomy Bridge"
  seoDescription={summary}
  schema={schema}
>
  <article class="max-w-[1120px] mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
    <header>
      <div class="max-w-[760px]">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Insights</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-8">
          Structured research on warehouse automation, robotics deployment, industrial AI, and 3PL
          markets.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
          Autonomy Bridge publishes analytical research for operators, investors, and vendors making
          high-stakes automation decisions. The Insights hub should read as a decision-grade research
          index, not a blog archive. It should surface the six active articles first, then clarify
          how the research connects to frameworks and applied use cases.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">What this hub covers</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-4 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
        <li>warehouse automation economics</li>
        <li>deployment failure patterns</li>
        <li>workflow architecture and bottlenecks</li>
        <li>vendor evaluation and scale risk</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Featured analysis</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-6">
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a href="/insights/why-warehouse-automation-projects-fail" class="hover:underline">
              Why Warehouse Automation Projects Fail
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Most warehouse automation failures originate during project underwriting, not deployment.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a href="/frameworks/automation-failure-framework" class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1">
              Automation Failure Framework
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a href="/insights/why-robotics-pilots-fail-to-scale" class="hover:underline">
              Why Robotics Pilots Fail to Scale
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Robotics pilots often prove technical feasibility without proving scale viability.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a
              href="/frameworks/pilot-to-scale-failure-framework"
              class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1"
            >
              Pilot-to-Scale Failure Framework
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a
              href="/insights/why-mid-market-operators-struggle-to-evaluate-warehouse-robotics"
              class="hover:underline"
            >
              Why Mid-Market Operators Struggle to Evaluate Warehouse Robotics
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Mid-market 3PL operators face structural evaluation barriers driven by variable demand
            and weak ROI assumptions.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a
              href="/frameworks/warehouse-automation-decision-framework"
              class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1"
            >
              Warehouse Automation Decision Framework
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-robotics-economics-actually-works" class="hover:underline">
              How Warehouse Robotics Economics Actually Works
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Warehouse automation ROI is governed by utilization and demand stability, not robot
            speed.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a href="/frameworks/robotics-roi-model" class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1">
              Robotics ROI Model
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-workflows-determine-automation-success" class="hover:underline">
              How Warehouse Workflows Determine Automation Success
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Workflow bottlenecks determine whether automation increases shipped volume or just
            relocates congestion.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a
              href="/frameworks/workflow-architecture-framework"
              class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1"
            >
              Workflow Architecture Framework
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="pb-6 border-b border-neutral-200 last:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
            <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-operators-evaluate-robotics-vendors" class="hover:underline">
              How Warehouse Operators Evaluate Robotics Vendors
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 mt-2">
            Vendor evaluation is a cross-functional process centered on utilization, integration, and
            economic fit.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
            Related framework:
            <a href="/frameworks/vendor-evaluation-framework" class="underline underline-offset-4 ml-1">
              Vendor Evaluation Framework
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Read by decision context</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <section class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-5 bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Economics and ROI</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
            <li>
              <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-robotics-economics-actually-works" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                How Warehouse Robotics Economics Actually Works
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/insights/why-warehouse-automation-projects-fail" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Why Warehouse Automation Projects Fail
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/frameworks/robotics-roi-model" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Robotics ROI Model
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-5 bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Workflow and operations</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
            <li>
              <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-workflows-determine-automation-success" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                How Warehouse Workflows Determine Automation Success
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/frameworks/workflow-architecture-framework" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Workflow Architecture Framework
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/use-cases/warehouse-automation-roi-evaluation" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Warehouse Automation ROI Evaluation
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 p-5 bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Vendor and deployment decisions</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800">
            <li>
              <a href="/insights/how-warehouse-operators-evaluate-robotics-vendors" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                How Warehouse Operators Evaluate Robotics Vendors
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/insights/why-robotics-pilots-fail-to-scale" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Why Robotics Pilots Fail to Scale
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/frameworks/vendor-evaluation-framework" class="underline underline-offset-4">
                Vendor Evaluation Framework
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">
        Related research infrastructure
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-[17px] leading-8 text-neutral-800 max-w-[760px]">
        Insights are linked to structured frameworks, applied use cases, case studies, and glossary
        terms so each article can be traced back to decision logic and implementation context.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-2 mt-6 text-sm">
        <a href="/frameworks" class="underline underline-offset-4">Frameworks</a>
        <a href="/use-cases" class="underline underline-offset-4">Use Cases</a>
        <a href="/case-studies" class="underline underline-offset-4">Case Studies</a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="underline underline-offset-4">Methodology</a>
        <a href="/glossary" class="underline underline-offset-4">Glossary</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</MainLayout>
